@NODE intro "Copyright © 1995-1996 Daniel [BigD] Lundqvist, CyberSoft"

  1. INTRODUCTION
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

Why another iconpackage ?
Don't you hate that the most of the icon replacement doesn't have all the
necessary icons or the icon is for the Hires-Interlaced screen modes.
I do, and it's therefor I begin to create my own icons. When I had over 150
icons I thought that is someone out there had the same problem as I have, so
it's therefor I created this iconpackage.

The package contents 154 different icons for the WB 2.04 up to 3.1. The most
icons have a alternate imagine but not all. Some of them contents just text,
and that's because I couldn't find a represent imagine. 
All of them is painted in the original WorkBench 4 colors, grey, black white
and blue, and has the same original icon size [55 x 22] (except the prefs
icons [60 x 26]). 
I have also added the original tooltype(s).

See Also: @{"How to install" LINK inst}
          @{"Which program I have used" LINK use}
@ENDNODE

@NODE req "Amiga Rules: PC Sucks!!"

  2. REQUIREMENTS
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

All you need is a Amiga running WorkBench 2.0 or higher.

The icons work even on a WorkBench 1.x, but the colors shouldn't be right.

See Also: @{"Installation" LINK inst}
@ENDNODE

@NODE inst "AmigaDOS Beats MS-DOS Any Time."

  3. INSTALLATION
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

@{u}Automatic@{uu}

Sorry, I haven't done any Installer script yet.

@{u}Manual@{uu}

This is very easy.
The only thing you need is the copy command.

Example:
@{b}Copy from RAM:cybericon12/CyberIcons/Utilities/Clock.info to
DH0:Utilities/Clock.info@{ub}

Or you can use such program as DirectoryOpus etc.

@{b}AND OF COURSE, DO NOT INSTALL TO YOUR ORIGINAL WORKBENCH 
DISK'S.@{ub}

Don't forget to change the tooltypes if you have done such things at the
original icons.

Se Also: @{"A list of all the icons." LINK lista}

@ENDNODE

